#week-title("One", "Philosophy of Distillation & The Distillation Train")

=== Core Teaching

Distillation is the operation by which the volatile is separated from the fixed
— the spirit lifted from the body, clarified, and captured. In the plant
kingdom, distillation produces hydrosols (the aromatic water) and, where
present, essential oils. These represent the Mercury and Sulphur of the plant,
freed from their earthy matrix by the agency of fire and cold.

Distillation is also the operation corresponding to the soul ascending to heaven
— the spirit leaving the body to be purified, before returning below enriched.

#doctrine[
  _"The alchemist uses distillation to study the nature of a plant's spirit: what
  rises first and most readily, and what refuses to rise at all."_
  #align(right)[— TTAO curriculum]
]

=== Topics This Week

- Distillation as the separation of subtle from gross
- Setting up a distillation train: flask, condenser, and receiver
- The role of fire and cold in the alchemical process

#inner-work[
  *The Angel of Temperance*

  Examine the Tarot card of *Temperance (Key 14)* carefully this month. This is
  the most directly alchemical image in the Major Arcana: an angelic figure
  pouring liquid between two vessels, one foot on land and one in water, with the
  sun rising behind. This is distillation itself.

  Meditate with this card each day this week. Observe the flow between the cups.
  Record your impressions in your Tarot journal.
]

